    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a pretty strong take. But couldn't you argue that the \"originalist\" perspective is just as valid? If they are looking at the actual text of the amendment as it was written at the time, isn't that a legitimate way to interpret the law, rather than just \"overreach\"?",
