      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The originalist perspective is a thinly veiled attempt to impose a 20th-century, gun-obsessed worldview on the Constitution, and it's a gross misreading of the Founders' intentions. The text of the Second Amendment is clear: it says \"a well-regulated Militia, being necessary to the security of a free State,\" not \"an individual right to bear arms.\" The originalists are cherry-picking historical context and ignoring the clear historical consensus that the Second Amendment was meant to apply to the collective right to bear arms in a militia, not individual gun ownership.",
      "source": "target",
